WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:45.930 --> 02:47.022
Shit.

04:27.230 --> 04:28.959
You pair of deuces
lookin' for work...

04:29.032 --> 04:32.398
I suggest you get your
scrawny asses in here pronto.

04:45.280 --> 04:47.009
Up on Brokeback...

04:47.082 --> 04:49.846
the Forest Service has got
designated campsites...

04:49.918 --> 04:51.579
on the allotments.

04:51.653 --> 04:55.646
Them camps can be 3, 4 miles
from where we pasture
the woollies.

04:55.724 --> 04:59.182
Bad predator loss
if there's nobody
lookin' after 'em at night.

04:59.261 --> 05:02.958
Now, what I want
is a camp tender...

05:04.032 --> 05:07.331
to stay in
the main camp, where
the Forest Service says.

05:07.403 --> 05:09.030
But the herder...

05:09.171 --> 05:12.140
he's gonna pitch a pup tent
on the QT with the sheep...

05:12.207 --> 05:14.266
and he's gonna sleep there.

05:14.343 --> 05:17.107
You eat your supper
and breakfast in camp...

05:17.179 --> 05:20.205
but you sleep
with the sheep 100%.

05:20.883 --> 05:23.374
No fire, don't leave no sign.

05:24.119 --> 05:25.609
You roll up that tent
every mornin'...

05:25.687 --> 05:27.120
in case Forest Service
snoops around.

05:29.291 --> 05:30.383
Yeah?

05:32.261 --> 05:33.285
No.

05:35.664 --> 05:36.653
No!

05:39.234 --> 05:41.224
Not on your fuckin' life.

05:44.238 --> 05:48.038
You got your dogs,
your .30-30, you sleep there.

05:48.643 --> 05:52.704
Last summer I had
goddamn near 25% loss.
I don't want that again.

05:53.247 --> 05:54.305
You.

05:55.850 --> 05:58.580
Fridays at noon,
be down at the bridge...

05:58.986 --> 06:01.386
with your grocery list
and mules...

06:01.456 --> 06:05.153
and somebody with supplies
will be there at the pick-up.

06:07.795 --> 06:11.094
Tomorrow mornin' we'll
truck you up to the jump-off.

06:39.527 --> 06:42.121
Jack Twist.
Ennis.

06:43.564 --> 06:46.829
Your folks
just stop at Ennis?
Del Mar.

06:48.503 --> 06:50.766
Well, nice to know you,
Ennis Del Mar.

07:09.189 --> 07:11.089
My second year up here.

07:12.325 --> 07:15.624
Last year, one storm,
the lightnin'
killed 42 sheep.

07:16.830 --> 07:19.424
Thought I'd asphyxiate
from the smell.

07:19.833 --> 07:24.236
Aguirre got all over my ass,
like I was supposed to
control the weather.

07:24.404 --> 07:28.534
But beats workin' for
my old man. Can't please
my old man, no way.

07:30.243 --> 07:33.906
That's why I took
to rodeoin'. You ever rodeo?

07:35.448 --> 07:38.349
You know, I mean,
once in a while.

07:39.085 --> 07:41.610
When I got the entry fee
in my pocket.

07:41.688 --> 07:42.780
Yeah.

07:44.190 --> 07:46.215
Are you from ranch people?

07:46.359 --> 07:47.758
Yeah, I was.

07:49.496 --> 07:51.396
Your folks run you off?

07:52.566 --> 07:55.364
No, they run themselves off.
There was...

07:56.770 --> 08:00.102
one curve in the road in
43 miles, and they miss it.

08:01.774 --> 08:04.572
So the bank took the ranch...

08:04.643 --> 08:07.737
and my brother and sister,
they raised me, mostly.

08:10.549 --> 08:12.744
Shit, that's hard.

08:17.957 --> 08:20.255
Can I? Thank you.

08:40.511 --> 08:41.740
Don't let them stray.

08:41.813 --> 08:43.748
Joe will have your ass
if you do.

08:43.816 --> 08:46.444
Only thing,
don't never order soup.

08:46.952 --> 08:49.352
Them soup boxes
are hard to pack.

08:49.855 --> 08:51.755
Well, I don't eat soup.

08:57.029 --> 09:00.726
You wanna watch it there.
That horse has
a low startle point.

09:01.266 --> 09:03.962
Doubt there's a filly
that could throw me.

09:04.603 --> 09:08.299
Let's git,
unless you wanna sit around
tyin' knots all day.

11:51.467 --> 11:52.559
Oh, shit.

11:52.902 --> 11:54.631
Can't wait till I get
my own spread...

11:54.703 --> 11:57.968
and I won't have
to put up with
Joe Aguirre's crap no more.

11:58.541 --> 12:00.771
I'm savin' for
a place myself.

12:02.912 --> 12:07.178
Alma and me, we're gonna
get married when I come
down off this mountain.

12:07.283 --> 12:10.446
Shit,
that stay with the sheep,
no fire bullshit.

12:11.921 --> 12:15.755
Aguirre got no right
makin' us do somethin'
against the rules.

13:05.106 --> 13:06.596
No more beans.

13:40.675 --> 13:42.870
Damn. Shit!

13:46.747 --> 13:48.874
I don't know.
Something wrong?

13:50.183 --> 13:51.377
Yeah, so what...

13:51.451 --> 13:54.079
Why didn't we get
the powdered milk
and the spuds?

13:54.154 --> 13:55.644
That's all we got.

13:56.256 --> 13:57.484
Well...

13:58.325 --> 14:00.020
Here's next week's.

14:02.529 --> 14:05.987
Thought you didn't eat soup.
Yeah, well,
I'm sick of beans.

14:06.066 --> 14:08.967
Too early in the summer
to be sick of beans.

14:11.738 --> 14:12.966
Come on.

14:35.862 --> 14:37.420
Come on. Come on.

14:48.809 --> 14:50.436
Hold on. Whoa, whoa!

14:54.081 --> 14:55.069
Shit.

14:56.182 --> 14:58.173
Whoa. Come back here!

15:36.655 --> 15:38.179
Whoa there, whoa.

15:38.324 --> 15:40.087
All right. Fuck it.

15:41.560 --> 15:43.460
Okay, you bastard.

15:46.799 --> 15:48.232
Where the hell you been?

15:48.300 --> 15:50.791
Been up with the sheep
all day, I get down here
hungry as hell...

15:50.870 --> 15:52.804
and all I find is beans.

15:57.209 --> 15:59.404
What in the hell happened,
Ennis?

15:59.678 --> 16:02.078
I come on a bear
is what happened.

16:02.348 --> 16:04.611
Goddamn horse spooked
and the mules took off...

16:04.682 --> 16:06.616
and scattered food
everywhere.

16:07.185 --> 16:10.951
Beans is about
all we got left.
Got whiskey or somethin'?

16:16.461 --> 16:17.951
Dumb-ass mule.

16:22.867 --> 16:26.098
I can't believe that.
God damn.

16:27.705 --> 16:29.297
Let me see.

16:35.280 --> 16:36.372
Shit.

16:36.915 --> 16:40.373
Well, we gotta do somethin'
about this food situation.

16:40.819 --> 16:43.253
Maybe I'll shoot
one of the sheep.

16:43.555 --> 16:45.989
Yeah, what if
Aguirre finds out, huh?

16:46.057 --> 16:48.025
We're supposed to guard
the sheep, not eat 'em.

16:48.093 --> 16:51.551
What's the matter with you?
There are a thousand of 'em.

16:52.697 --> 16:54.562
I'll stick with beans.

16:56.868 --> 16:58.358
Well, I won't.

17:12.250 --> 17:13.273
Yeah!

17:13.351 --> 17:15.978
Gettin' tired
of your dumb-ass missin'.

17:16.220 --> 17:17.653
Let's get a move on.

17:17.721 --> 17:20.690
Don't want the Game and Fish
to catch us with no elk.

17:45.516 --> 17:47.677
Come on. Shit.

17:54.725 --> 17:57.250
Yeah, I'm commutin'
four hours a day.

17:58.095 --> 18:01.189
I come in for breakfast,
I go back to the sheep.

18:01.565 --> 18:03.692
Evenin',
get 'em bedded down.

18:03.767 --> 18:06.531
Come in for supper,
go back to the sheep.

18:07.571 --> 18:10.631
Spend half the night
checkin' for damn coyotes.

18:11.441 --> 18:14.069
Aguirre got no right
to make me do this.

18:16.880 --> 18:19.178
You wanna switch?
I wouldn't mind
sleepin' out there.

18:19.249 --> 18:23.083
That ain't the point.
The point is, we both
ought to be in this camp.

18:23.886 --> 18:27.014
Goddamn pup tent smells
like cat piss or worse.

18:27.790 --> 18:30.122
I wouldn't mind
bein' out there.

18:33.462 --> 18:35.794
Well, I'm happy
to switch with you...

18:35.865 --> 18:38.459
but I warn you,
I can't cook worth a damn.

18:39.068 --> 18:41.901
I am pretty good
with a can opener, though.

18:42.805 --> 18:45.296
You can't be no worse
than me, then.

18:46.175 --> 18:47.574
Here you go.

18:57.653 --> 19:00.019
You won't get much sleep,
I'll tell you that.

19:00.089 --> 19:01.818
Yup. Come on.

19:21.544 --> 19:23.512
Shot a coyote up there.

19:24.447 --> 19:28.144
It's a big son of a bitch.
He had balls on him
the size of apples.

19:29.118 --> 19:31.985
He looked like
he could eat himself a camel.

19:33.488 --> 19:35.786
You want
some of this hot water?

19:39.494 --> 19:41.018
It's all yours.

20:07.389 --> 20:08.481
Mmm.

20:20.201 --> 20:22.192
I don't rodeo much myself.

20:22.971 --> 20:24.131
I mean,
what's the point...

20:24.205 --> 20:26.867
of ridin' some piece of stock
for eight seconds?

20:26.941 --> 20:29.967
Money's a good point.
True enough.

20:31.446 --> 20:34.142
If you don't get stomped
winnin' it, huh?

20:34.282 --> 20:35.374
Yeah.

20:37.152 --> 20:40.246
Well, my old man,
he was a bull rider.

20:41.990 --> 20:43.320
Thank you.

20:44.091 --> 20:46.286
Pretty well-known in his day.

20:46.694 --> 20:49.288
Though he kept his secrets
to himself.

20:50.698 --> 20:54.225
Never taught me a thing,
never once come
to see me ride.

21:05.779 --> 21:08.475
Your brother and sister
do right by you?

21:09.116 --> 21:12.552
They did the best they could
after my folks was gone.

21:14.421 --> 21:17.254
Considerin' they didn't
leave us nothin'...

21:17.591 --> 21:19.684
but $24 in a coffee can.

21:21.261 --> 21:23.627
I got me
a year of high school.

21:24.398 --> 21:27.595
That was before
the transmission went
on the pickup.

21:30.371 --> 21:34.068
And then my sis left.
She married a roughneck,
moved to Casper.

21:35.209 --> 21:36.938
And me and my brother...

21:37.010 --> 21:40.537
we went and got ourselves
some work on a ranch
up near Worland.

21:40.614 --> 21:43.549
Till I was 19.
Then he got married.

21:46.186 --> 21:48.120
And no more room for me.

21:51.525 --> 21:55.153
That's how come
me end up here.

22:05.338 --> 22:06.430
What?

22:08.241 --> 22:12.143
Man, that's more words
than you've spoke
in the past two weeks.

22:13.012 --> 22:15.845
Hell, that's the most
I've spoke in a year.

22:21.821 --> 22:24.153
But my dad,
he was a fine roper.

22:25.258 --> 22:26.555
Didn't rodeo much, though.

22:26.626 --> 22:29.220
He thought rodeo cowboys
was all fuck-ups.

22:32.131 --> 22:33.792
The hell they are.

22:35.468 --> 22:36.696
Well...

22:42.608 --> 22:43.836
There you go.

22:45.645 --> 22:49.411
I'm spurrin' his guts out!
Wavin' to the girls
in the stands!

22:49.482 --> 22:53.043
He's kickin' me to
high heaven, but he don't
jackboard me! No!

22:57.256 --> 22:59.247
I think my dad was right.

23:44.469 --> 23:46.334
Tent don't look right.

23:47.038 --> 23:49.871
Well, it ain't
goin' nowhere. Let it be.

23:51.810 --> 23:54.278
That harmonica don't sound
quite right either.

23:54.346 --> 23:57.782
That's 'cause
it got kind of flattened
when that mare threw me.

23:57.849 --> 23:59.441
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

24:00.051 --> 24:02.952
I thought you said
that mare couldn't throw you.

24:03.021 --> 24:04.511
She got lucky.

24:05.957 --> 24:09.484
Yeah, well, if I got lucky,
that harmonica
would've broke in two.

24:12.963 --> 24:17.195
# I know I shall meet you
on that final day #

24:17.768 --> 24:22.762
# Water-walking Jesus,
take me away! ##

24:24.441 --> 24:27.069
Very good.
Oh, yeah.

24:27.278 --> 24:30.372
My mama, she believes
in the Pentecost.

24:30.447 --> 24:31.709
Oh, yeah?

24:33.884 --> 24:35.852
What exactly
is the Pentecost?

24:35.920 --> 24:38.684
I mean, my folks,
they was Methodist.

24:40.124 --> 24:41.614
The Pentecost.

24:41.926 --> 24:44.417
I don't know, I don't know
what the Pentecost is.

24:44.495 --> 24:48.955
Mom never explained it to me.
I guess it's when
the world ends...

24:49.133 --> 24:52.193
and fellas like you and me,
we march off to hell.

24:53.370 --> 24:54.962
Speak for yourself.

24:55.039 --> 24:58.566
You may be a sinner,
but I ain't yet had
the opportunity.

25:01.178 --> 25:02.509
Thank you.

25:05.382 --> 25:07.282
Shit!

25:09.219 --> 25:11.119
I'm gonna go up
to the sheep now.

25:11.188 --> 25:12.678
Give 'em hell.

25:18.796 --> 25:20.319
No, I'm...

25:22.465 --> 25:25.992
You can hardly stand.
It's too late to go
to them sheep.

25:29.772 --> 25:31.763
Well, you got
an extra blanket?

25:31.908 --> 25:35.742
I'll just roll up out here,
grab 40 winks...

25:36.145 --> 25:38.545
and I'll ride out
at first light.

25:42.585 --> 25:45.281
You'll freeze your ass off
when that fire dies down.

25:45.355 --> 25:46.652
Oh, that's good.

25:46.723 --> 25:48.691
You're better off
sleepin' in the tent.

25:48.758 --> 25:49.850
Yeah.

25:51.527 --> 25:52.858
All right.

26:29.265 --> 26:31.596
Ennis!
What?

26:32.234 --> 26:34.964
Just quit your yammerin'
and get in here!

27:36.298 --> 27:38.425
Come on, come on.

27:47.675 --> 27:49.404
What are you doin'?

29:56.402 --> 29:58.130
See you for supper.

29:59.538 --> 30:01.028
Yeah. Come on.

30:39.077 --> 30:40.339
Come on.

32:05.229 --> 32:08.062
This is a one-shot thing
we got goin' on here.

32:13.437 --> 32:15.735
It's nobody's business
but ours.

32:17.440 --> 32:19.340
You know I ain't queer.

32:20.410 --> 32:21.775
Me, neither.

33:36.618 --> 33:37.949
I'm sorry.

33:39.121 --> 33:40.645
It's all right.

33:42.858 --> 33:44.348
It's all right.

33:44.426 --> 33:46.485
Lie back. Come on.

34:49.657 --> 34:50.817
Twist.

34:51.458 --> 34:54.223
Your Uncle Harold's in
the hospital with pneumonia.

34:54.295 --> 34:56.592
Docs don't expect
he'll make it.

34:57.532 --> 35:00.626
Your ma sent me to tell you,
so here I am.

35:03.771 --> 35:05.033
Bad news.

35:06.874 --> 35:09.536
There ain't nothin' I can do
about it up here, I guess.

35:09.610 --> 35:13.171
There's not much you can do
about it down there, neither.

35:15.950 --> 35:18.384
Not unless you can
cure pneumonia.

35:51.451 --> 35:53.681
God damn! Jesus!

35:53.787 --> 35:56.654
Them sheep will drift
if I don't get back
up there tonight!

35:56.723 --> 35:59.715
You'll get
pitched off your mount
in a storm like this.

35:59.793 --> 36:02.091
You'll wish
you hadn't tried it!

36:02.862 --> 36:04.796
It's too cold! Close it up!

36:14.574 --> 36:17.099
What are we
supposed to do now, huh?

36:17.244 --> 36:21.476
Get on in there and
untangle 'em Chilean sheep
out of ours, I guess.

36:23.350 --> 36:25.011
Oh, where is it? Shit!

36:29.256 --> 36:32.419
God, half the goddamn
paint brands have wore off!

36:33.393 --> 36:37.625
We gotta try.
The least we can do is get
the count right for Aguirre.

36:37.697 --> 36:40.495
Fuck Aguirre!
Oh, yeah, fuck Aguirre.

36:40.634 --> 36:43.501
What if we need to
work for him again?
You think of that?

36:43.570 --> 36:45.800
We gotta
stick this out, Jack.

37:01.654 --> 37:05.181
You'll run them
sheep off again
if you don't quiet down.

37:41.660 --> 37:43.389
What are you doing?

37:44.663 --> 37:46.528
Aguirre came by again.

37:47.032 --> 37:49.500
Says my uncle didn't die
after all.

37:50.202 --> 37:51.897
Says bring 'em down.

37:51.970 --> 37:55.064
Bring 'em down, why?
It's the middle of August.

37:55.341 --> 37:58.504
Says there's a storm comin',
movin' in from the Pacific.

37:58.577 --> 38:00.340
Worse than this one.

38:01.046 --> 38:04.344
That snow barely
stuck an hour. Huh?

38:06.117 --> 38:09.985
Besides, that son of a bitch,
he's cuttin' us out
a whole month's pay.

38:10.054 --> 38:11.453
It ain't right.

38:13.658 --> 38:14.886
Well...

38:15.259 --> 38:17.853
I can spare you a loan, bud,
if you're short on cash.

38:17.929 --> 38:19.794
Give it to you
when we get to Signal.

38:19.864 --> 38:21.855
I don't need your money, huh?

38:22.233 --> 38:25.361
You know, I ain't in
the poorhouse. Shit!

38:27.105 --> 38:28.436
All right.

39:01.539 --> 39:03.564
Time to get goin', cowboy.

39:18.021 --> 39:20.114
Come here!
This ain't no rodeo, cowboy!

39:20.190 --> 39:21.487
Oh, shit!

39:48.151 --> 39:50.176
Ennis. Ennis.

39:53.757 --> 39:55.918
Come here. You okay?

39:56.660 --> 39:58.150
You okay?
Yeah.

40:48.010 --> 40:50.843
Some of these never went
up there with you.

40:53.849 --> 40:56.511
Count ain't what
I'd hoped for, neither.

40:57.419 --> 41:00.718
You ranch stiffs,
you ain't never no good.

41:15.838 --> 41:17.738
Wanna give it some gas?

41:26.782 --> 41:29.774
I can't believe I left
my damn shirt up there.

41:31.887 --> 41:32.978
Yeah.

41:35.790 --> 41:37.883
You gonna do this again
next summer?

41:37.959 --> 41:39.324
Well, maybe not.

41:40.061 --> 41:43.497
Like I said, me and Alma is
gettin' married in November.

41:43.565 --> 41:44.691
So...

41:45.533 --> 41:48.263
I'll try to get somethin'
on a ranch, I guess.

41:49.370 --> 41:50.598
And you?

41:52.173 --> 41:56.507
Might go up to my daddy's
place and give him
a hand through the winter.

41:58.079 --> 41:59.671
I might be back.

42:00.515 --> 42:02.506
If the Army don't get me.

42:08.423 --> 42:10.823
Well, I guess
I'll see you around, huh?

42:11.859 --> 42:13.019
Right.

43:23.697 --> 43:26.757
What the fuck
are you lookin' at? Huh?

43:35.409 --> 43:37.001
<i>"And forgive us</i>
<i>our trespasses...</i>

43:37.077 --> 43:39.841
<i>"as we forgive those</i>
<i>who trespass against us.</i>

43:39.913 --> 43:43.349
"Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

43:43.450 --> 43:47.750
"For thine is the kingdom,
the power and the glory,
forever. Amen."

43:49.222 --> 43:51.086
Under the powers
vested in me...

43:51.157 --> 43:53.751
I now pronounce you
man and wife.

43:54.694 --> 43:58.061
You may kiss the bride.
And if you don't, I will.

44:16.382 --> 44:18.350
You all right?
No.

44:22.421 --> 44:23.513
Stop!

44:24.724 --> 44:26.055
No, please don't!

44:31.997 --> 44:34.659
My old lady's tryin' to
get me to quit this job.

44:34.734 --> 44:38.534
She says I'm gettin' too old
to be breakin' my back
shovelin' asphalt.

44:38.604 --> 44:42.301
I told her strong backs
and weak minds
runs in the family.

44:42.908 --> 44:45.376
She didn't think
that was too funny.

44:45.444 --> 44:47.537
I told her it keeps me fit.

44:50.449 --> 44:52.815
<i>Mornin'.</i>
<i>Mornin'.</i>

44:54.353 --> 44:58.119
<i>Pulled in last night.</i>
<i>Didn't want to wake you up.</i>

44:58.357 --> 45:00.188
<i>Oh, no, I was just...</i>

45:01.960 --> 45:04.258
<i>I thought I'd tell you</i>
<i>before the Sergeant</i>
<i>showed up.</i>

45:04.329 --> 45:06.593
<i>Parking this trailer</i>
<i>on the beach is illegal.</i>

45:25.750 --> 45:26.842
Yeah!

45:33.191 --> 45:35.284
Well,
look what the wind blew in.

45:36.060 --> 45:37.584
Hi, Mr. Aguirre.

45:37.662 --> 45:40.790
I was wonderin' if you was
needin' any help this summer.

45:40.865 --> 45:43.095
You're wastin'
your time here.

45:44.235 --> 45:46.362
What, you ain't got nothin'?

45:48.006 --> 45:49.974
Nothin' up on Brokeback?

45:51.843 --> 45:53.970
I ain't got no work for you.

46:02.587 --> 46:05.317
Ennis Del Mar
ain't been around, has he?

46:08.493 --> 46:12.053
You boys sure found a way
to make the time pass
up there.

46:14.331 --> 46:15.525
Twist...

46:15.999 --> 46:18.968
you guys wasn't gettin' paid
to leave the dogs
baby-sit the sheep...

46:19.036 --> 46:21.129
while you stemmed the rose.

46:26.743 --> 46:29.268
Now get the hell
out of my trailer.

47:15.158 --> 47:16.887
How my girls doing?

47:18.161 --> 47:21.061
All right. Jenny's still
got a runny nose.

47:44.387 --> 47:46.981
Ennis, could you wipe
Alma Jr.'s nose?

47:47.456 --> 47:49.686
If I had three hands,
I could.

47:51.060 --> 47:53.028
Come here. Come here. Oh!

48:20.990 --> 48:22.252
Girls all right?

48:22.325 --> 48:26.091
Yeah.
Jenny stopped her coughin'.

48:27.897 --> 48:30.262
I think I should take
the girls into town
this weekend.

48:30.332 --> 48:33.768
Get 'em an ice cream.
Somethin'.

48:38.006 --> 48:39.871
Can't we move to town?

48:41.776 --> 48:44.472
I'm tired of these
lonesome old ranches.

48:45.580 --> 48:48.640
No one's around
for Junior to play with.

48:48.950 --> 48:50.611
Besides,
I'm scared for Jenny...

48:50.685 --> 48:53.518
scared if she has another one
of 'em bad asthma spells.

48:53.588 --> 48:55.783
No, rent in town
is too high.

48:59.427 --> 49:02.885
There's a cheap place
in Riverton,
over the Laundromat.

49:03.465 --> 49:05.899
I bet I could
fix it up real nice.

49:06.134 --> 49:09.365
I bet you could fix
this place up real nice
if you wanted to.

49:09.437 --> 49:10.836
Ennis.
Hmm?

49:11.840 --> 49:14.206
I know you'd like it, too.

49:15.744 --> 49:19.840
Real home, other kids
for the girls to play with.

49:23.051 --> 49:25.542
Not so lonely
like you were raised.

49:26.955 --> 49:29.753
You don't want 'em
to be so lonely, do you?

49:33.995 --> 49:35.189
Yeah.

49:37.599 --> 49:38.929
Come here.

49:44.705 --> 49:46.935
It ain't so lonely now,
is it?

49:52.012 --> 49:54.810
Are you sure
the girls are asleep?
Yeah.

50:07.761 --> 50:09.092
Come here.

50:21.075 --> 50:22.235
Ennis.

50:24.745 --> 50:26.906
<i>Let 'er rip and snort, boys!</i>

50:26.980 --> 50:29.505
<i>Jack Twist,</i>
<i>hangin' on for dear life!</i>

50:29.850 --> 50:33.684
<i>And down he goes!</i>
<i>Watch out there, fella!</i>

50:33.754 --> 50:36.484
<i>He's comin' for you.</i>
<i>Send in the clowns!</i>

50:37.491 --> 50:40.221
<i>Okay, a fine ride</i>
<i>by Mr. Twist.</i>
Shit!

50:40.294 --> 50:41.818
<i>Four seconds for him.</i>

50:42.830 --> 50:46.527
<i>Give 'em a hand, folks,</i>
<i>our very own rodeo clowns!</i>

50:49.969 --> 50:51.493
Give us a beer, Doug.

51:04.817 --> 51:07.251
I'd like to buy
Jimbo here a beer.

51:09.088 --> 51:11.989
Best damn rodeo clown
I've ever worked with.

51:14.393 --> 51:15.758
No thanks, cowboy.

51:15.828 --> 51:18.194
If I was to let
every rodeo hand
I pulled a bull off of...

51:18.264 --> 51:21.165
buy me liquor, I'd have
been a alcoholic long ago.

51:27.473 --> 51:30.670
