57:34.535 --> 57:36.162
Oh, wait, hold on.

57:38.405 --> 57:40.930
You don't think
I'm too fast, do you?

57:41.242 --> 57:43.676
Maybe we should
put the brakes on?

57:44.310 --> 57:47.643
Fast or slow, I just like
the direction you're goin'.

57:58.157 --> 58:00.990
You are in a hurry.
My daddy's the hurry.

58:01.060 --> 58:03.790
He expects me home
with the car by midnight.

58:14.440 --> 58:16.465
Come here, come here.

58:17.911 --> 58:19.139
Hi, Monroe.
Hey, Ennis.

58:19.212 --> 58:20.201
Is Alma here?

58:20.280 --> 58:21.645
Yeah, she's in
the condiments aisle.

58:21.714 --> 58:23.477
The what?
Ketchup.

58:23.883 --> 58:25.077
Thanks.

58:25.485 --> 58:26.975
Your boy gonna play
again this year?

58:27.053 --> 58:28.543
Excuse us!
Yeah, excuse me.

58:28.621 --> 58:31.317
Hey, honey. Honey,
what are y'all doing here?

58:31.624 --> 58:32.682
Big hurry.

58:32.759 --> 58:35.694
My boss called and,
well, he wants me to
go up to the ranch.

58:35.762 --> 58:36.751
Mama.

58:36.829 --> 58:38.421
I guess all the heifers
must've decided...

58:38.498 --> 58:40.022
To calve at the same time.

58:40.099 --> 58:42.067
I figured I could
drop the girls off with you.

58:42.135 --> 58:43.568
Ennis, well...

58:43.636 --> 58:46.264
I got a million things
I gotta do here
before I can leave.

58:46.339 --> 58:47.897
I don't get off
for another three hours.

58:47.974 --> 58:50.943
Mama, I need crayons.
Not now, Alma.

58:51.344 --> 58:53.937
Ennis, please, you promised
you'd take them tonight.

58:54.012 --> 58:56.776
Alma, I can't afford
not to be there
when the heifers calve.

58:56.848 --> 58:58.816
Right, it'd be my job
if I lose any of 'em.

58:58.884 --> 59:00.545
What about my job?

59:04.356 --> 59:06.221
Okay, all right,
I'll call my sister.

59:06.291 --> 59:08.691
I'll see if she can take 'em.
All right. All right.

59:08.760 --> 59:10.887
You be a good girl
for your mama, all right?

59:10.963 --> 59:12.294
I'll be half the night.

59:12.364 --> 59:14.298
Bring home some ground steaks
if you think of it.

59:14.366 --> 59:17.733
Come here. Oh, Alma, please!

59:21.073 --> 59:22.301
Oh, boy.

59:23.041 --> 59:24.838
Okay.
Monroe, I'm so sorry.

59:24.910 --> 59:27.003
It's okay. It's okay, Alma.

59:27.279 --> 59:29.645
I'll clean this up
just as soon as
I call my sister...

59:29.715 --> 59:30.841
to come get the girls.

59:30.916 --> 59:33.316
Really, Alma, it's okay.
I'll get it.

59:33.385 --> 59:35.979
Alma, come with me.
Watch your feet.

59:36.188 --> 59:37.280
Alma.

59:38.924 --> 59:40.255
It's just like my hand.

59:40.325 --> 59:42.486
Honey,
got a surprise for you.

59:42.961 --> 59:44.121
Hey.

59:46.231 --> 59:48.961
I got two whole boxes
of formula for you.

59:49.034 --> 59:50.058
You did?

59:50.135 --> 59:53.104
120 cans.
120?

59:53.171 --> 59:54.661
L.D., where did you put 'em?

59:54.740 --> 59:57.675
Oh, hell,
back seat of the car,
where I left 'em.

59:59.745 --> 01:00:01.474
Rodeo can get 'em.

01:00:04.248 --> 01:00:08.150
L.D., I can already see
who little Bobby looks like.

01:00:08.252 --> 01:00:09.412
Good job, little girl.

01:00:09.487 --> 01:00:12.115
He's the spittin' image
of his grandpa.

01:00:13.090 --> 01:00:16.184
Isn't he just the spittin'
image of his grandpa?

01:00:18.863 --> 01:00:19.921
Yeah.

01:00:22.733 --> 01:00:24.530
Look at those eyes.

01:00:50.227 --> 01:00:51.285
Hey.

01:00:53.964 --> 01:00:55.329
Hey, honey.

01:00:59.403 --> 01:01:02.133
Hey, Ennis, you know
somebody, name of Jack?

01:01:05.409 --> 01:01:06.774
Maybe. Why?

01:01:06.911 --> 01:01:09.812
'Cause you got a postcard.
It come general delivery.

01:01:22.192 --> 01:01:24.990
Is he somebody
you cowboyed with, or what?

01:01:25.995 --> 01:01:28.088
No, Jack, he rodeos, mostly.

01:01:31.267 --> 01:01:33.167
We was fishin' buddies.

01:02:11.875 --> 01:02:13.809
You can color that one, too.

01:02:13.877 --> 01:02:15.868
I'll color the beach.

01:02:22.317 --> 01:02:25.218
Maybe we could
get a baby-sitter.
Huh?

01:02:27.189 --> 01:02:29.248
Take your friend
to the Knife and Fork?

01:02:29.324 --> 01:02:31.815
No, Jack ain't
the restaurant type.

01:02:32.594 --> 01:02:35.495
We'll more likely
just go out and get drunk.

01:02:36.899 --> 01:02:38.628
That's if he shows.

01:02:44.273 --> 01:02:48.107
Okay, we take one more bite,
and then you're finished
with dinner.

01:02:48.744 --> 01:02:52.111
There, that's a good bite.
All right, you're excused.

01:02:52.447 --> 01:02:54.108
Please. Thank you.

01:03:14.736 --> 01:03:16.465
Jack fuckin' Twist.

01:03:21.176 --> 01:03:22.700
Son of a bitch.

01:03:28.550 --> 01:03:29.710
Come here.

01:04:30.378 --> 01:04:33.142
Alma, this is Jack Twist.

01:04:34.282 --> 01:04:35.715
And, Jack,
this is my wife, Alma.

01:04:35.783 --> 01:04:37.375
Howdy.
Hello.

01:04:39.487 --> 01:04:40.647
You got a kid.

01:04:40.720 --> 01:04:43.746
Yeah, I got two little girls.
Alma Jr. And Jenny.

01:04:44.291 --> 01:04:46.020
I got a boy.
Yeah?

01:04:46.626 --> 01:04:49.151
Eight months old.
Smiles a lot.

01:04:50.630 --> 01:04:52.860
I married
the prettiest little gal
in Childress, Texas.

01:04:52.933 --> 01:04:54.457
Yeah?
Lureen.

01:04:57.270 --> 01:05:00.967
So me and Jack,
we're gonna head out and
get ourselves a drink. Yeah?

01:05:01.741 --> 01:05:04.209
Sure enough.
Pleased to meet you, ma'am.

01:05:04.644 --> 01:05:05.975
We might not
get back tonight...

01:05:06.046 --> 01:05:08.241
when we get to drinkin'
and talkin' and all.

01:05:08.315 --> 01:05:09.441
Ennis?

01:05:10.383 --> 01:05:11.850
Would you get me
a pack of smokes?

01:05:11.918 --> 01:05:14.819
If you need smokes, Alma,
they're in the top pocket
of my blue shirt.

01:05:14.888 --> 01:05:16.515
There in the bedroom.

01:05:28.134 --> 01:05:31.626
Four years. Damn!
Yeah, four years.

01:05:34.874 --> 01:05:37.069
Didn't think
I'd hear from you again.

01:05:37.978 --> 01:05:40.674
I figured you were sore
from that punch.

01:05:41.514 --> 01:05:44.449
Right next summer,
I drove back up to Brokeback.

01:05:44.517 --> 01:05:46.644
Talked to Aguirre
about a job, and...

01:05:46.720 --> 01:05:49.382
He told me you hadn't
been back, so I left.

01:05:50.056 --> 01:05:53.115
Went down to Texas
for rodeoin'.

01:05:54.059 --> 01:05:56.027
That's how I met Lureen.

01:05:56.895 --> 01:06:00.058
Made $2,000 that year,
bull ridin'. Nearly starved.

01:06:02.101 --> 01:06:05.502
Lureen's old man
makes serious money,
farm machine business.

01:06:05.571 --> 01:06:07.664
Of course, he hates my guts.

01:06:12.077 --> 01:06:15.240
And the Army didn't get you?
No, too busted up.

01:06:15.447 --> 01:06:17.745
And rodeoin' ain't what
it was in my daddy's day.

01:06:17.816 --> 01:06:20.216
Got out
while I could still walk.

01:06:22.321 --> 01:06:26.280
Swear to God,
I didn't know we was
goin' to get into this again.

01:06:29.028 --> 01:06:31.019
Yes I did.
I red-lined it all the way.

01:06:31.096 --> 01:06:33.121
I couldn't get here
fast enough.

01:06:33.799 --> 01:06:37.360
What about you?
Me? I don't know.

01:06:41.206 --> 01:06:42.673
I don't know.

01:06:48.180 --> 01:06:50.705
Old Brokeback got us good,
don't it?

01:06:56.188 --> 01:06:58.315
What are we gonna do now?

01:07:02.193 --> 01:07:04.627
I doubt there's nothin'
we can do.

01:07:09.133 --> 01:07:11.431
So now I'm stuck
with what I got here.

01:07:16.074 --> 01:07:19.168
Makin' a livin' is
about all I got time for now.

01:07:43.201 --> 01:07:44.259
Hey.

01:07:44.569 --> 01:07:47.367
Well, me and Jack is
headed up the mountain
for a day or two.

01:07:47.438 --> 01:07:49.668
Do ourselves
a little fishin'.

01:07:56.848 --> 01:08:00.375
You know, your friend
could come inside,
have a cup of coffee.

01:08:00.551 --> 01:08:02.178
Well, he's from Texas.

01:08:03.221 --> 01:08:05.280
Texans don't drink coffee?

01:08:14.865 --> 01:08:17.026
You sure that foreman won't
fire you for takin' off?

01:08:17.100 --> 01:08:19.033
You know, that foreman,
he owes me.

01:08:19.102 --> 01:08:22.935
I worked through a blizzard
last Christmas.
You remember that?

01:08:23.240 --> 01:08:25.868
Besides, I'll only be
a couple of days.

01:08:29.279 --> 01:08:31.474
Bring fish, Daddy.
A big, big one!

01:08:38.555 --> 01:08:40.283
Come here. Come here.

01:08:46.395 --> 01:08:47.727
Come here.

01:08:50.966 --> 01:08:52.867
See you Sunday, latest.

01:09:03.313 --> 01:09:05.178
I'm starvin'. Want to
get somethin' to eat?

01:09:05.247 --> 01:09:06.272
Yup.

01:09:34.577 --> 01:09:36.044
Last one in!

01:09:54.830 --> 01:09:57.993
Is there anything interestin'
up there in heaven?

01:09:58.234 --> 01:10:00.964
Well, I was just sending up
a prayer of thanks.

01:10:01.637 --> 01:10:02.899
For what?

01:10:04.773 --> 01:10:07.537
For you forgettin'
to bring that harmonica.

01:10:07.610 --> 01:10:10.010
I'm enjoying
the peace and quiet.

01:10:14.250 --> 01:10:17.742
You know
it could be like this,
just like this, always.

01:10:18.621 --> 01:10:20.816
Yeah? How do you figure that?

01:10:24.560 --> 01:10:27.825
What if you and me had
a little ranch somewhere...

01:10:29.297 --> 01:10:32.733
a little
cow-and-calf operation?
It'd be a sweet life.

01:10:32.967 --> 01:10:34.901
I mean, hell,
Lureen's old man...

01:10:34.969 --> 01:10:37.062
you bet he'd give me
a down payment to get lost.

01:10:37.138 --> 01:10:39.834
I mean, he more or less
already said it.

01:10:41.175 --> 01:10:42.403
No, I...

01:10:44.412 --> 01:10:47.404
I told you
it ain't gonna be that way.

01:10:50.418 --> 01:10:51.783
You know...

01:10:52.620 --> 01:10:55.680
you got your wife
and baby in Texas.

