seem to wanna dance
with their wives.

01:35:03.048 --> 01:35:04.879
Why do you think
that is, Jack?

01:35:04.950 --> 01:35:07.418
I don't know,
I never give it any thought.

01:35:08.320 --> 01:35:09.719
Wanna dance?

01:35:11.123 --> 01:35:13.591
Yes, thank you.
Do you mind?

01:35:13.659 --> 01:35:16.526
No, it's all right. Go ahead.
All right.

01:35:17.563 --> 01:35:18.791
Pardon us.

01:35:18.864 --> 01:35:20.661
Thank you for asking me
to dance with you.

01:35:20.733 --> 01:35:22.894
I really appreciate that.
Randall never does.

01:35:22.968 --> 01:35:24.765
Last time I did,
I think it was our wedding.

01:35:24.837 --> 01:35:27.203
It's a good thing
you and Lureen happened
along when you did...

01:35:27.272 --> 01:35:29.399
or else we'd still be stuck
on the side of the road...

01:35:29.475 --> 01:35:30.737
in that darn pickup.

01:35:30.809 --> 01:35:32.299
I told Randall
we ought to take the car.

01:35:32.377 --> 01:35:33.901
Of course,
he'd never listen to me.

01:35:33.979 --> 01:35:36.971
He wouldn't listen to me
if he was goin' deaf tomorrow.

01:35:37.049 --> 01:35:40.109
I told him it'd take more than
chewing gum and baling wire...

01:35:40.185 --> 01:35:41.743
to fix that pickup.

01:35:41.820 --> 01:35:43.947
Well, he's never been
very mechanical, though.

01:35:46.825 --> 01:35:48.690
Come over here and ask...

01:35:55.466 --> 01:35:57.593
You ever notice how a woman
will powder her nose...

01:35:57.668 --> 01:35:59.602
before she goes to a party?

01:35:59.670 --> 01:36:03.106
And then she'll powder it
again once the party's over.

01:36:03.407 --> 01:36:06.899
I mean, why powder your nose
just to go home and go to bed?

01:36:06.978 --> 01:36:08.309
Don't know.

01:36:09.147 --> 01:36:10.512
Even if I wanted to know...

01:36:10.581 --> 01:36:13.846
I couldn't get
a word in with Lashawn
long enough to ask.

01:36:13.918 --> 01:36:17.251
Woman talks a blue streak.
Lively little gal.

01:36:25.196 --> 01:36:27.289
You'll like working
for Roy Taylor.

01:36:27.365 --> 01:36:30.562
He's solid, Roy.
Yeah, Roy.
He's a good old boy.

01:36:35.973 --> 01:36:38.806
He's got a little cabin
down on Lake Kemp.

01:36:40.144 --> 01:36:42.544
Got a crappie house,
little boat.

01:36:43.080 --> 01:36:45.605
Said I could use it
whenever I want.

01:36:49.353 --> 01:36:51.981
We ought to go down there
some weekend.

01:36:52.824 --> 01:36:55.258
Drink a little whiskey,
fish some.

01:36:56.661 --> 01:36:58.925
Get away, you know?

01:37:02.133 --> 01:37:03.623
That was right out of SMU.

01:37:03.701 --> 01:37:06.168
I could've had
my pick of pretty much
any job in North Dallas.

01:37:06.236 --> 01:37:08.602
So my pick was Neiman Marcus,
which was a disaster...

01:37:08.672 --> 01:37:11.766
because, honey,
where clothes is concerned,
I got no resistance.

01:37:11.842 --> 01:37:15.107
I was spending more than
I made. More than
Randall ever will make.

01:37:15.178 --> 01:37:16.167
We come out here...

01:37:16.246 --> 01:37:18.339
thinkin' that ranchin' was
still big hats and Mariboros.

01:37:18.415 --> 01:37:20.349
Boy, were we behind the times.

01:37:36.967 --> 01:37:39.162
Hey there, Junior. You ready?

01:37:40.804 --> 01:37:43.272
##

01:37:54.417 --> 01:37:56.146
What do you think?

01:37:56.987 --> 01:38:00.286
Your daddy ever gonna see
fit to settle down again?

01:38:01.625 --> 01:38:04.992
Don't know. Maybe he's not
the marrying kind.

01:38:07.964 --> 01:38:09.693
You don't think so?

01:38:10.367 --> 01:38:12.995
Or you don't think
I'm the one for him?

01:38:15.771 --> 01:38:17.500
You're good enough.

01:38:22.578 --> 01:38:25.775
You don't say much,
but you get your point across.

01:38:27.950 --> 01:38:30.282
Sorry.
I didn't mean to be rude.

01:38:33.188 --> 01:38:34.280
All right.

01:38:35.124 --> 01:38:37.649
You're stayin'
on your feet, cowboy.

01:38:38.761 --> 01:38:40.251
Excuse me, darling.

01:39:03.152 --> 01:39:06.815
So I'll pick you and Jenny up
next weekend, after church.

01:39:08.290 --> 01:39:09.382
Fine.

01:39:13.062 --> 01:39:14.552
You all right?

01:39:15.864 --> 01:39:16.922
Yes.

01:39:18.133 --> 01:39:19.600
Are you sure?

01:39:22.871 --> 01:39:26.033
Daddy, I was thinking,
what with the new baby
and all...

01:39:26.107 --> 01:39:28.507
Ma and Monroe have been
awful strict on me.

01:39:28.576 --> 01:39:30.669
More on me than Jenny even.

01:39:31.579 --> 01:39:33.911
I was thinkin',
maybe I could...

01:39:36.084 --> 01:39:38.484
Maybe I could come
stay with you.

01:39:39.654 --> 01:39:42.487
I'd be an awful good help,
I know I would.

01:39:42.924 --> 01:39:45.916
Now, you know
I ain't set up for that.

01:39:47.762 --> 01:39:49.889
With the roundup comin'...

01:39:50.565 --> 01:39:52.362
I won't ever be home.

01:39:53.868 --> 01:39:55.733
It's all right, Daddy.

01:39:56.004 --> 01:39:59.963
I'm not sayin'
that I wouldn't...
It's all right, I understand.

01:40:02.343 --> 01:40:04.573
Well, see you on Sunday, then.

01:40:05.546 --> 01:40:06.604
Bye.

01:40:09.150 --> 01:40:10.742
Bye, sweetheart.

01:40:40.280 --> 01:40:42.578
Going to snow
tonight for sure.

01:40:43.817 --> 01:40:44.875
Yup.

01:40:52.526 --> 01:40:55.984
All this time and you ain't
found nobody else to marry?

01:40:57.798 --> 01:40:59.197
I been puttin' the blocks...

01:40:59.266 --> 01:41:02.133
to a good-lookin' little gal
over in Riverton.

01:41:03.637 --> 01:41:07.539
She's a waitress.
Wants to go to nursing school
or somethin'.

01:41:10.510 --> 01:41:11.875
I don't know.

01:41:15.382 --> 01:41:17.407
What about you and Lureen?

01:41:19.920 --> 01:41:22.718
Lureen's good
at making hard deals in
the machinery business...

01:41:22.789 --> 01:41:25.223
but as far as
our marriage goes...

01:41:25.759 --> 01:41:27.989
we could do it over the phone.

01:41:37.904 --> 01:41:40.634
I kind of got this thing
going with...

01:41:41.541 --> 01:41:44.202
a ranch foreman's wife
over in Rutters.

01:41:44.577 --> 01:41:46.238
What?
I'm bound to get shot...

01:41:46.312 --> 01:41:49.645
by Lureen or her husband
each time I slip off
to see her.

01:41:50.816 --> 01:41:52.841
You probably deserve it.

01:41:59.792 --> 01:42:01.350
Tell you what.

01:42:06.398 --> 01:42:07.922
The truth is...

01:42:14.907 --> 01:42:18.206
sometimes I miss you so much,
I can hardly stand it.

01:43:00.485 --> 01:43:03.215
I guess I'll head up
on to Lightning Flat.

01:43:04.589 --> 01:43:06.887
See the folks
for a day or two.

01:43:12.797 --> 01:43:15.994
There's somethin' I been
meanin' to tell you, bud.

01:43:20.104 --> 01:43:23.596
Well, it's likely November
before I can come out
here again.

01:43:27.011 --> 01:43:31.243
After we ship stock and before
winter feedin' starts again.

01:43:35.153 --> 01:43:36.381
November.

01:43:40.458 --> 01:43:43.188
What in the hell ever happened
to August?

01:43:44.095 --> 01:43:45.084
Well...

01:43:48.266 --> 01:43:49.756
Christ, Ennis.

01:43:55.740 --> 01:43:59.904
You know, you had
a fucking week to say
some little word about this.

01:44:02.412 --> 01:44:04.846
Why is it we're always
in the friggin' cold?

01:44:04.915 --> 01:44:07.509
We ought to go south
where it's warm, you know!

01:44:07.584 --> 01:44:09.575
We ought to go to Mexico.

01:44:10.420 --> 01:44:11.614
Mexico?

01:44:12.956 --> 01:44:15.447
Hell, Jack, you know me.
About all the travelin'
I ever done...

01:44:15.525 --> 01:44:18.585
is around a coffee pot,
looking for the handle.

01:44:21.031 --> 01:44:23.363
Come on, Jack.
Lighten up on me.

01:44:25.469 --> 01:44:27.437
We can hunt in November.

01:44:28.272 --> 01:44:30.001
Kill us a nice elk.

01:44:32.542 --> 01:44:34.407
I'll try if I can get
Don Wroe's cabin again.

01:44:34.478 --> 01:44:37.174
We had a good time that year,
didn't we?

01:44:39.816 --> 01:44:42.512
There's never enough time,
never enough.

01:44:46.990 --> 01:44:48.719
You know, friend...

01:44:49.826 --> 01:44:53.284
this is a goddamn bitch of
an unsatisfactory situation.

01:44:54.364 --> 01:44:57.993
You used to come away easy.
Now it's like seein' the Pope.

01:45:00.971 --> 01:45:02.734
Jack, I got to work.

01:45:05.842 --> 01:45:08.743
In them earlier days,
I'd just quit the job.

01:45:11.480 --> 01:45:12.811
You...

01:45:13.482 --> 01:45:16.747
You forget what it's like
bein' broke all the time.

01:45:20.356 --> 01:45:22.654
You ever hear
of child support?

01:45:26.529 --> 01:45:28.861
I'll tell you this,
I can't quit this one...

01:45:28.931 --> 01:45:30.922
and I can't get the time off.

01:45:34.870 --> 01:45:36.861
It was hard enough
gettin' this time.

01:45:36.939 --> 01:45:38.668
The trade-off was August.

01:45:42.812 --> 01:45:44.677
Well, you got a better idea?

01:45:47.483 --> 01:45:48.882
I did, once.

01:45:51.087 --> 01:45:52.577
You did, once.

01:45:57.426 --> 01:45:59.951
Well, have you been to Mexico,
Jack Twist?

01:46:02.631 --> 01:46:06.158
'Cause I hear what they got
in Mexico for boys like you.

01:46:07.903 --> 01:46:11.464
Hell, yes,
I've been to Mexico.
Is that a fucking problem?

01:46:19.548 --> 01:46:22.948
I'm going to tell you this
one time, Jack fucking Twist.

01:46:23.017 --> 01:46:24.780
And I ain't foolin'.

01:46:26.121 --> 01:46:29.784
What I don't know, all them
things that I don't know...

01:46:30.191 --> 01:46:33.092
could get you killed
if I come to know them.

01:46:37.265 --> 01:46:38.789
I ain't jokin'.

01:46:43.605 --> 01:46:46.267
Yeah, well try this one,
and I'll say it just once.

01:46:46.341 --> 01:46:49.037
Go ahead!
I'll tell you what.

01:46:49.110 --> 01:46:50.577
We could have had
a good life together.

01:46:50.645 --> 01:46:53.842
Fucking real good life.
Had us a place of our own!

01:46:54.883 --> 01:46:56.942
But you didn't want it, Ennis.

01:46:57.018 --> 01:46:59.816
So what we got now
is Brokeback Mountain!

01:47:02.056 --> 01:47:05.355
Everything's built on that!
That's all we got, boy.
Fucking all.

01:47:05.427 --> 01:47:08.055
So I hope you know that,
if you don't never know
the rest!

01:47:08.129 --> 01:47:10.393
God damn it.
You count the damn
few times...

01:47:10.465 --> 01:47:12.262
that we have been together
in nearly 20 years...

01:47:12.333 --> 01:47:14.460
and you measure
the short fucking leash
you keep me on...

01:47:14.536 --> 01:47:17.164
and then you ask me
about Mexico and you tell me
you'll kill me...

01:47:17.238 --> 01:47:20.298
for needin' somethin'
I don't hardly never get!

01:47:22.877 --> 01:47:25.812
You have no idea
how bad it gets!

01:47:29.350 --> 01:47:32.284
And I'm not you!
I can't make it...

01:47:32.352 --> 01:47:35.879
on a couple of high-altitude
fucks once or twice a year!

01:47:38.459 --> 01:47:40.757
You are too much
for me, Ennis.

01:47:41.462 --> 01:47:43.589
You son of a whoreson bitch!

01:47:45.766 --> 01:47:47.996
I wish I knew how to quit you!

01:47:50.637 --> 01:47:52.366
Then why don't you?

01:47:55.309 --> 01:47:57.743
Why don't you just
let me be, huh?

01:47:59.813 --> 01:48:02.805
It's because of you, Jack,
that I'm like this.

01:48:06.453 --> 01:48:07.852
I'm nothin'.

01:48:08.522 --> 01:48:09.921
I'm nowhere.

01:48:14.595 --> 01:48:17.223
It's okay.
Get the fuck off me!

01:48:24.304 --> 01:48:26.898
It's all right.
It's all right.

01:48:27.975 --> 01:48:29.567
Damn you, Ennis.

01:48:30.911 --> 01:48:33.505
I just can't stand
this anymore, Jack.

01:48:44.023 --> 01:48:47.481
Come on now, you're sleepin'
on your feet like a horse.

01:48:49.829 --> 01:48:52.992
My mama used to say that to me
when I was little.

01:48:54.033 --> 01:48:55.728
And sing to me.

01:49:09.582 --> 01:49:10.981
I got to go.

01:49:13.920 --> 01:49:15.854
See you in the morning.

01:49:56.761 --> 01:49:58.854
##

01:50:11.009 --> 01:50:12.340
Excuse me.

01:50:17.415 --> 01:50:18.473
Hey.

01:50:19.451 --> 01:50:20.941
Ennis Del Mar.

01:50:24.522 --> 01:50:26.046
Where you been?

01:50:28.026 --> 01:50:29.550
Here and there.

01:50:32.230 --> 01:50:35.358
I left word for you
with Steve at the ranch.

01:50:36.267 --> 01:50:39.634
And you must've got those
notes I left at your place.

01:50:43.441 --> 01:50:46.239
Looks like I got the message,
in any case.

01:50:48.480 --> 01:50:49.572
Carl?

01:50:51.416 --> 01:50:53.384
Yeah, Carl's nice.

01:50:54.152 --> 01:50:55.642
He even talks.

01:50:58.856 --> 01:51:00.323
Good for you.

01:51:02.693 --> 01:51:03.785
Yeah.

01:51:06.797 --> 01:51:08.196
Good for me.

01:51:14.638 --> 01:51:16.936
I don't get you,
Ennis Del Mar.

01:51:22.279 --> 01:51:23.610
I'm sorry.

01:51:32.089 --> 01:51:34.614
I was probably
no fun anyways, was I?

01:51:38.095 --> 01:51:41.030
Ennis, girls don't
fall in love with fun.

01:52:23.773 --> 01:52:27.436
Hello.
<i>Hello, this is Ennis Del Mar.</i>

01:52:30.747 --> 01:52:32.374
Who? Who is this?

01:52:33.950 --> 01:52:36.748
Ennis Del Mar.
I'm an old buddy of Jack's.

01:52:37.854 --> 01:52:39.947
<i>Jack used to mention you.</i>

01:52:40.323 --> 01:52:44.020
You're the fishing buddy
or the hunting buddy,
I know that.

01:52:45.094 --> 01:52:46.857
Would have let you know
what happened...

01:52:46.929 --> 01:52:49.454
but I wasn't sure
about your name or address.

01:52:49.532 --> 01:52:52.467
Jack kept his friends'
addresses in his head.

01:52:54.370 --> 01:52:57.305
That's why I'm callin',
to see what happened.

01:52:59.308 --> 01:53:00.832
Oh, yeah.

01:53:03.279 --> 01:53:06.214
Jack was pumpin' up a flat
on the truck...

01:53:06.315 --> 01:53:09.045
out on a back road,
when the tire blew up.

01:53:09.185 --> 01:53:12.086
The rim of the tire slammed
into his face...

01:53:12.288 --> 01:53:16.190
broke his nose and jaw
and knocked him unconscious
on his back.

01:53:17.459 --> 01:53:20.917
<i>By the time somebody</i>
<i>come along, he'd drowned</i>
<i>in his own blood.</i>

01:53:22.030 --> 01:53:24.021
<i>He was only 39 years old.</i>

01:53:28.637 --> 01:53:31.071
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

01:53:32.307 --> 01:53:33.535
<i>Hello.</i>

01:53:37.179 --> 01:53:39.170
Was he buried down there?

01:53:39.915 --> 01:53:41.348
We put a stone up.

01:53:41.817 --> 01:53:43.842
He was cremated,
like he wanted.

01:53:43.919 --> 01:53:48.185
Half his ashes was
interred here, the rest was
sent up with his folks.

01:53:49.457 --> 01:53:53.484
He use to say he wanted
his ashes scattered
on Brokeback Mountain...

01:53:53.562 --> 01:53:55.962
<i>but I wasn't sure</i>
<i>where that was.</i>

01:53:56.331 --> 01:54:00.097
<i>I thought</i>
<i>Brokeback Mountain might be</i>
<i>around where he grew up.</i>

01:54:00.168 --> 01:54:01.465
<i>Knowing Jack...</i>

01:54:01.536 --> 01:54:03.800
it might be some
pretend place...

01:54:03.872 --> 01:54:07.069
where bluebirds sing
and there's a whiskey spring.

01:54:10.045 --> 01:54:11.478
No, ma'am...

01:54:12.547 --> 01:54:15.675
we was herdin' sheep
on Brokeback one summer...

01:54:16.318 --> 01:54:17.717
<i>back in '63.</i>

01:54:27.161 --> 01:54:29.857
Well, he said
it was his favorite place.

01:54:31.232 --> 01:54:34.429
I thought he meant to
get drunk. He drank a lot.

01:54:37.638 --> 01:54:40.505
Is his folks still up
in Lightning Flat?

01:54:41.175 --> 01:54:43.871
<i>They'll be there</i>
<i>till the day they die.</i>

01:54:48.916 --> 01:54:50.884
Thank you for your time.

01:54:51.752 --> 01:54:53.344
<i>I sure am sorry.</i>

01:54:54.588 --> 01:54:56.351
<i>We was good friends.</i>

01:55:03.530 --> 01:55:05.760
Get in touch with his folks.

01:55:05.833 --> 01:55:09.633
I suppose they'd appreciate it
if his wishes was carried out.

01:55:11.472 --> 01:55:13.440
About the ashes, I mean.

01:56:14.233 --> 01:56:17.669
Want a cup of coffee,
don't you?
Piece of cherry cake?

01:56:17.737 --> 01:56:19.295
Yes, ma'am,
I'll have a cup of coffee...

01:56:19.372 --> 01:56:22.535
but I can't eat no cake
just now. Thank you.

01:56:31.217 --> 01:56:33.378
I feel awful bad about Jack.

01:56:36.222 --> 01:56:37.553
Thank you.

01:56:39.525 --> 01:56:42.323
I can't begin to tell you
how bad I feel.

01:56:45.330 --> 01:56:47.230
I knew him a long time.

01:56:50.135 --> 01:56:52.103
I come by to say that...

01:56:52.771 --> 01:56:56.400
if you want me to take his
ashes up there on Brokeback...

01:56:57.142 --> 01:56:59.576
like his wife said
he wanted to...

01:57:00.345 --> 01:57:02.142
then I'll be happy to.

01:57:05.250 --> 01:57:06.979
I'll tell you what.

01:57:08.053 --> 01:57:10.453
I know where
Brokeback Mountain is.

01:57:11.723 --> 01:57:15.853
Thought he was too goddamn
special to be buried
in the family plot.

01:57:19.264 --> 01:57:20.993
Jack used to say...

01:57:21.833 --> 01:57:24.495
"Ennis Del Mar,"
he used to say.

01:57:26.171 --> 01:57:29.436
"I'm gonna bring him up here
one of these days...

01:57:30.075 --> 01:57:33.010
"and we'll lick this
damn ranch into shape."

01:57:34.446 --> 01:57:36.277
He had some
half-baked notion...

01:57:36.348 --> 01:57:38.942
the two of you was gonna
move up here...

01:57:39.418 --> 01:57:41.010
build a cabin...

01:57:42.054 --> 01:57:43.783
help run the place.

01:57:47.359 --> 01:57:49.088
Then, this spring...

01:57:50.695 --> 01:57:53.926
he got another fella
gonna come up here with him...

01:57:55.599 --> 01:57:58.796
build the place,
help run the ranch.

01:57:59.804 --> 01:58:04.241
Some ranch neighbor of his
from down in Texas.

01:58:06.310 --> 01:58:09.643
Gonna split up with his wife
and come back here...

01:58:10.414 --> 01:58:11.779
so he says.

01:58:13.617 --> 01:58:15.949
But, like most of
Jack's ideas...

01:58:17.788 --> 01:58:19.517
never come to pass.

01:58:22.660 --> 01:58:26.528
I kept his room
like it was when he was a boy.

01:58:27.932 --> 01:58:30.059
I think he appreciated that.

01:58:34.605 --> 01:58:37.802
You are welcome to go up
to his room, if you want.

01:58:43.481 --> 01:58:45.779
Yeah, I'd like that.
Thank you.

02:01:46.961 --> 02:01:48.553
Tell you what.

02:01:51.065 --> 02:01:54.796
We got a family plot.
He's goin' in it.

02:01:57.471 --> 02:01:58.733
Yes, sir.

02:02:01.342 --> 02:02:03.640
You come back
and see us again.

02:02:17.958 --> 02:02:19.448
Thank you, ma'am.

02:03:14.214 --> 02:03:16.148
##

02:03:17.250 --> 02:03:19.912
Hey there, Junior.
Hey, Daddy.

02:03:28.762 --> 02:03:30.059
Come here.

02:03:32.866 --> 02:03:34.333
Like the car?

02:03:34.801 --> 02:03:37.599
Yeah. Is it yours?
It's Kurt's.

02:03:38.338 --> 02:03:41.432
I thought you were
seein' Troy.
Troy?

02:03:42.007 --> 02:03:44.237
Daddy, that was two years ago.

02:03:45.677 --> 02:03:47.975
Troy still playing baseball?

02:03:48.347 --> 02:03:51.544
I don't know what he's doing.
I'm seein' Kurt now.

02:03:51.950 --> 02:03:55.113
Well, what does Kurt do?
Works out in the oil fields.

02:03:56.889 --> 02:04:00.222
So he's a roughneck, huh?
Yeah.

02:04:01.059 --> 02:04:04.893
I guess you're 19,
you can do whatever you want.
Isn't that right?

02:04:04.963 --> 02:04:06.260
Sure.

02:04:14.873 --> 02:04:17.933
Daddy,
you need more furniture.
Yeah, well...

02:04:18.577 --> 02:04:21.410
if you got nothin',
you don't need nothin'.

02:04:25.684 --> 02:04:27.652
So, what's the occasion?

02:04:32.090 --> 02:04:33.580
Me and Kurt...

02:04:34.893 --> 02:04:36.758
we're getting married.

02:04:39.531 --> 02:04:40.930
Well...

02:04:41.733 --> 02:04:44.258
So how long have you
known this guy for?

02:04:44.436 --> 02:04:45.903
About a year.

02:04:47.906 --> 02:04:51.273
Our wedding will be June 5,
at the Methodist church.

02:04:51.576 --> 02:04:55.376
Jenny will be singing
and Monroe is gonna cater
the reception.

02:05:01.853 --> 02:05:03.844
Now this Kurt fella...

02:05:06.190 --> 02:05:07.657
he loves you?

02:05:10.428 --> 02:05:12.020
Yeah, Daddy.

02:05:13.297 --> 02:05:14.696
He loves me.

02:05:22.740 --> 02:05:24.765
Was hopin' you'd be there.

02:05:27.545 --> 02:05:28.671
Yeah.

02:05:31.949 --> 02:05:36.443
I think I'm supposed to be
on a roundup down near
the Tetons.

02:05:57.375 --> 02:05:58.967
You know what?

02:06:00.311 --> 02:06:03.370
I reckon they can find
themselves a new cowboy.

02:06:05.181 --> 02:06:08.708
My little girl,
getting married.

02:06:22.332 --> 02:06:24.391
To Alma and Kurt.

02:07:44.880 --> 02:07:46.677
Jack, I swear...

